<task id="task_m5t_sf1_pvb">
    <title>Encrypting Config File for Installation</title>
    <taskbody>
        <context id="context_ob3_1dg_pvb"><ph conkeyref="PRODvars/PRODUCT_SP_ALTERNATIVE_NAME"
                >OFFICIAL_PRODUCT_NAME</ph> supports encrypting the configuration file for
            installation to prevent sensitive data leakage. The encrypted configuration file name is
            fixed to
                <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="153,255,255"?><filepath>Setup.bin</filepath><?oxy_custom_end?></context>
        <steps id="steps_yvn_3mg_pvb">
            <step>
                <cmd>Prepare your <ph conkeyref="PRODvars/SETUP_FILE"/> as mentioned in <xref
                        href="silent_installation_intro_sp_agent=20221122135932.xml"/></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Encrypt <ph conkeyref="PRODvars/SETUP_FILE"/> by using the command prompt:
                        <userinput>StellarProtectSetup.exe -e &lt;CONFIG_FILE></userinput>. The
                    parameter <codeph>-e</codeph> is used for encrypting the configuration file and
                    generating
                        <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="153,255,255"?><filepath>Setup.bin</filepath><?oxy_custom_end?>
                    file in the working directory.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>After the
                        <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="153,255,255"?><filepath>Setup.bin</filepath><?oxy_custom_end?>
                    file is generated. place it in the installer package.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>The installation with encrypted configuration can now be executed.</cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
